<br>
It wasn't one bad member of a guild that bullied their way into Fionna's camp, it was a significant portion of a guild.<br>
<br>
By virtue of wearing the Landslide guildtag, you give tacit approval of the actions of the camp stealers.<br>
<br>
Lodizal and VS have nothing to do with this.<br>
<br>
The GM is not at fault for Landslide's lack of consideration and honor.<br>
<br>
Verant may have created a shitty camp, but it doesn't excuse bullying and camp stealing.<br>
<br>
There is nothing wrong with not grouping or aiding Landslide members over this incident, just as there is nothing wrong with refusing to hire a pedophiliac as your babysitter.  In fact, given Landslide's actions and the &quot;it's just a game&quot; attitude the guild's members have presented here, I think anyone would be within their rights to take over a camp inhabited by LS members and to expect no complaints.  But I think most of us regard personal and guild honor too highly to do such things.<br>
<br>
If it's just a game then there was no reason for you to trample over other players in such a manner.  Of course, one could say that the Olympiad is just a bunch of games or that World Cup soccer is just a game, but it seems a bit simplistic to me to describe them that way.  Same with EQ (though perhaps not on such a grand scale as the examples).<br>
<br>
Landslide has made its bed, now they must lie in it.<br>
