I really feel with Fionna who had to sit there for so long, to get booted out.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
By your own statement, you feel some guilt over what was done here. People usually don't feel guilty over nothing. Your guild did something wrong, and you clearly know it here despite all justifications you make. If you acted honourably and respectably here, you would not feel sorry in any way.<br>
<br>
I think Palimax sums it up very nicely with this statement: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> By virtue of wearing the Landslide guildtag, you give tacit approval of the actions of the camp stealers.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
So even though you know your guild wrong, you continue to associate with this guild and wear its tag. Are you trying to justify Landslide's actions to the rest of us or to yourself?<br>
<br>
